{
  "info": {
    "_postman_id": "auth-login-e2e",
    "name": "Auth \u2013 Login (POST /api/v1/auth/login)",
    "description": "E2E tests for POST /api/v1/auth/login.\n\nFolder execution order (orchestrated by make e2e-login):\n  1. setup          \u2014 register a fresh user, fetch OTP from Gmail, verify email\n  2. validation     \u2014 422/413 input-error cases (no setup required)\n  3. happy-path     \u2014 200 + access_token body + refresh_token cookie checks\n  4. failures       \u2014 wrong password, unknown identifier, unverified account\n  5. rate-limiting  \u2014 IP limiter exhaustion: 5 warmups, 6th \u2192 429\n\nAll test users use @e2e.test or the fixed gmail_test_email address.\nRun `make _e2e-db-clean` and `make _e2e-kv-clean` before this collection.\n\nNotes on what is NOT covered here (already covered by internal tests):\n  - Cookie MaxAge derived from expires_at       \u2014 handler_test.go TestHandler_Login_CookieMaxAgeDerivedFromRefreshExpiry\n  - Secure flag when SecureCookies=true          \u2014 handler_test.go TestHandler_Login_CookieSecureTrue_WhenSecureCookiesEnabled\n  - Plain ErrLoginLocked without Retry-After     \u2014 handler_test.go\n  - Zero RetryAfter clamped to 1                 \u2014 handler_test.go\n  - Token mint failure \u2192 500                     \u2014 handler_test.go TestHandler_Login_TokenMintError\n  - All error responses have code + JSON CT      \u2014 handler_test.go\n\nNotes on what is NOT covered here (requires special DB setup or seed scripts):\n  - Valid username + password \u2192 200              \u2014 username not settable via public register API;\n                                                   store_test.go covers the DB lookup path.\n                                                   Needs a Makefile target that seeds a username row.\n  - Inactive account \u2192 403 account_inactive      \u2014 requires UPDATE users SET is_active=false in DB.\n                                                   Add a seed script or Makefile target to cover this.\n  - Admin-locked \u2192 423 account_locked            \u2014 requires UPDATE users SET is_locked=true in DB.\n                                                   Add a seed script or Makefile target to cover this.\n  - Time-locked \u2192 429 login_locked + Retry-After \u2014 achievable by hammering wrong passwords until\n                                                   login_locked_until is set; depends on MaxLoginAttempts\n                                                   config. Defer until that constant is exposed in .env.",
    "schema": "https://schema.getpostman.com/json/collection/v2.1.0/collection.json"
  },
  "event": [
    {
      "listen": "prerequest",
      "script": {
        "type": "text/javascript",
        "exec": [
          "// Increment the request sequence counter and derive a unique X-Forwarded-For IP",
          "// for every request so non-RL folders never exhaust any rate-limit bucket.",
          "// The rate-limiting folder overrides _xff to 127.0.0.1 via its own prerequest.",
          "// Requires TRUSTED_PROXIES=127.0.0.1/32 in .env.",
          "const n = (pm.collectionVariables.get('_req_seq') | 0) + 1;",
          "pm.collectionVariables.set('_req_seq', n);",
          "const ip = '10.' + ((n>>16)&0xff) + '.' + ((n>>8)&0xff) + '.' + (n&0xff);",
          "pm.collectionVariables.set('_xff', ip);"
        ]
      }
    }
  ],
  "item": [
    {
      "name": "setup",
      "description": "Registers the gmail_test_email user, fetches the OTP from Gmail, and verifies the email. The happy-path and failures folders depend on lgn_happy_email / lgn_happy_password being set here and email_verified=true in the DB.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /register \u2192 201 (setup user)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const email = pm.environment.get('gmail_test_email');",
                  "if (!email) {",
                  "    console.error('[ERROR] gmail_test_email not set in environment \u2014 add it to environment.json.');",
                  "}",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('lgn_happy_email', email);",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('lgn_happy_password', 'P@ssw0rd1!');"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));",
                  "pm.test('message field present and non-empty', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().message).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty);",
                  "",
                  "const token = pm.variables.get('gmail_access_token');",
                  "if (!token) { console.warn('[WARN] gmail_access_token not set \u2014 skipping Gmail fetch'); return; }",
                  "",
                  "console.log('[INFO] Waiting 8 s for verification email to arrive in Gmail...');",
                  "const start = Date.now();",
                  "while (Date.now() - start < 8000) {}",
                  "console.log('[INFO] Done waiting. Querying Gmail API (async)...');",
                  "",
                  "const query = encodeURIComponent('subject:\"Verify your\" newer_than:1h');",
                  "pm.sendRequest({",
                  "    url: 'https://gmail.googleapis.com/gmail/v1/users/me/messages?q=' + query + '&maxResults=3',",
                  "    method: 'GET',",
                  "    header: { Authorization: 'Bearer ' + token }",
                  "}, (err, res) => {",
                  "    if (err) { console.error('[ERROR] Gmail list failed:', err); return; }",
                  "    if (res.code === 401) { console.error('[ERROR] Gmail token expired'); return; }",
                  "    const msgs = res.json().messages;",
                  "    if (!msgs || !msgs.length) { console.warn('[WARN] No matching email found in Gmail.'); return; }",
                  "    pm.sendRequest({",
                  "        url: 'https://gmail.googleapis.com/gmail/v1/users/me/messages/' + msgs[0].id + '?format=full',",
                  "        method: 'GET',",
                  "        header: { Authorization: 'Bearer ' + token }",
                  "    }, (err2, res2) => {",
                  "        if (err2) { console.error('[ERROR] Gmail fetch failed:', err2); return; }",
                  "        const msg = res2.json();",
                  "        let body = '';",
                  "        const parts = msg.payload && msg.payload.parts;",
                  "        if (parts && parts.length) {",
                  "            const p = parts.find(x => x.mimeType === 'text/plain') || parts.find(x => x.mimeType === 'text/html');",
                  "            if (p && p.body && p.body.data) body = atob(p.body.data.replace(/-/g, '+').replace(/_/g, '/'));",
                  "        } else if (msg.payload && msg.payload.body && msg.payload.body.data) {",
                  "            body = atob(msg.payload.body.data.replace(/-/g, '+').replace(/_/g, '/'));",
                  "        }",
                  "        if (!body) { console.warn('[WARN] Could not decode email body.'); return; }",
                  "        const match = body.match(/(?<!#)\\b(\\d{6})\\b/);",
                  "        if (!match) { console.warn('[WARN] No 6-digit OTP found in email body.'); return; }",
                  "        pm.collectionVariables.set('lgn_code', match[1]);",
                  "        console.log('[INFO] OTP stored in lgn_code:', match[1]);",
                  "    });",
                  "});"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\"display_name\": \"LgnHappy\", \"email\": \"{{lgn_happy_email}}\", \"password\": \"{{lgn_happy_password}}\"}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/register",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "register"]
            }
          }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /verification \u2192 200 (consume OTP)",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "prerequest",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "const code = pm.collectionVariables.get('lgn_code');",
                  "if (!code) {",
                  "    console.error('[ERROR] lgn_code is empty \u2014 Gmail fetch did not complete.');",
                  "    console.error('        Check: gmail_access_token is set and not expired, --delay-request >= 8000.');",
                  "}"
                ]
              }
            },
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "pm.test('message includes \"verified\"', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().message).to.include('verified'));"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": {
            "method": "POST",
            "header": [
              { "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" },
              { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }
            ],
            "body": {
              "mode": "raw",
              "raw": "{\"email\": \"{{lgn_happy_email}}\", \"code\": \"{{lgn_code}}\"}",
              "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } }
            },
            "url": {
              "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/verification",
              "host": ["{{base_url}}"],
              "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "verification"]
            }
          }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "validation",
      "description": "All input-validation cases for POST /login.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "malformed JSON \u2192 400",
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": ["pm.test('status is 400', () => pm.response.to.have.status(400));", "pm.test('code is bad_request', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().code).to.eql('bad_request'));"] } }],
          "request": { "method": "POST", "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }, { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }], "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{bad json", "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } } }, "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "login"] } }
        },
        {
          "name": "empty body \u2192 422",
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": ["pm.test('status is 422', () => pm.response.to.have.status(422));", "pm.test('code is validation_error', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().code).to.eql('validation_error'));"] } }],
          "request": { "method": "POST", "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }, { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }], "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "", "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } } }, "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "login"] } }
        },
        {
          "name": "missing identifier \u2192 422",
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": ["pm.test('status is 422', () => pm.response.to.have.status(422));", "pm.test('code is validation_error', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().code).to.eql('validation_error'));"] } }],
          "request": { "method": "POST", "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }, { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }], "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"password\": \"P@ssw0rd1!\"}", "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } } }, "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "login"] } }
        },
        {
          "name": "empty identifier \u2192 422",
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": ["pm.test('status is 422', () => pm.response.to.have.status(422));", "pm.test('code is validation_error', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().code).to.eql('validation_error'));"] } }],
          "request": { "method": "POST", "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }, { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }], "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"identifier\": \"\", \"password\": \"P@ssw0rd1!\"}", "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } } }, "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "login"] } }
        },
        {
          "name": "missing password \u2192 422",
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": ["pm.test('status is 422', () => pm.response.to.have.status(422));", "pm.test('code is validation_error', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().code).to.eql('validation_error'));"] } }],
          "request": { "method": "POST", "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }, { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }], "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"identifier\": \"user@e2e.test\"}", "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } } }, "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "login"] } }
        },
        {
          "name": "body > 1 MiB \u2192 413",
          "event": [
            { "listen": "prerequest", "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": ["const pad = 'x'.repeat(1024 * 1024 + 1);", "pm.request.body.update({ mode: 'raw', raw: JSON.stringify({ identifier: 'bigbody@e2e.test', password: 'P@ssw0rd1!', _pad: pad }) });"] } },
            { "listen": "test", "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": ["pm.test('status is 413', () => pm.response.to.have.status(413));"] } }
          ],
          "request": { "method": "POST", "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }, { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }], "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{}", "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } } }, "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "login"] } }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "happy-path",
      "description": "Uses the verified account created by the setup folder.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "POST /login valid email+password \u2192 200 with access_token and refresh_token cookie",
          "event": [
            {
              "listen": "test",
              "script": {
                "type": "text/javascript",
                "exec": [
                  "pm.test('status is 200', () => pm.response.to.have.status(200));",
                  "const body = pm.response.json();",
                  "pm.test('access_token field present and non-empty', () => { pm.expect(body).to.have.property('access_token'); pm.expect(body.access_token).to.be.a('string').and.not.empty; });",
                  "pm.test('body does not contain password field', () => pm.expect(body).to.not.have.property('password'));",
                  "const setCookieHeader = pm.response.headers.get('Set-Cookie') || '';",
                  "pm.test('refresh_token cookie present in Set-Cookie', () => { pm.expect(setCookieHeader).to.include('refresh_token='); });",
                  "pm.test('refresh_token cookie is HttpOnly', () => { pm.expect(setCookieHeader.toLowerCase()).to.include('httponly'); });",
                  "pm.test('refresh_token cookie Path is /api/v1/auth', () => { pm.expect(setCookieHeader).to.include('Path=/api/v1/auth'); });",
                  "pm.test('refresh_token cookie SameSite is Strict', () => { pm.expect(setCookieHeader).to.include('SameSite=Strict'); });",
                  "pm.test('refresh_token cookie has positive Max-Age', () => { const match = setCookieHeader.match(/Max-Age=(\\d+)/); pm.expect(match).to.not.be.null; pm.expect(parseInt(match[1], 10)).to.be.above(0); });",
                  "pm.collectionVariables.set('lgn_access_token', body.access_token);"
                ]
              }
            }
          ],
          "request": { "method": "POST", "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }, { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }], "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"identifier\": \"{{lgn_happy_email}}\", \"password\": \"{{lgn_happy_password}}\"}", "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } } }, "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "login"] } }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "failures",
      "description": "Credential-failure and account-state failure paths.",
      "item": [
        {
          "name": "wrong password \u2192 401 invalid_credentials",
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": ["pm.test('status is 401', () => pm.response.to.have.status(401));", "const body = pm.response.json();", "pm.test('code is invalid_credentials', () => pm.expect(body.code).to.eql('invalid_credentials'));", "pm.collectionVariables.set('lgn_wrong_pw_body', JSON.stringify(body));"] } }],
          "request": { "method": "POST", "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }, { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }], "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"identifier\": \"{{lgn_happy_email}}\", \"password\": \"Wr0ng!Password\"}", "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } } }, "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "login"] } }
        },
        {
          "name": "POST /register \u2192 201 (setup unverified user)",
          "event": [
            { "listen": "prerequest", "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": ["pm.collectionVariables.set('lgn_unverified_email', 'lgn-unvfy-' + Date.now() + '@e2e.test');", "pm.collectionVariables.set('lgn_unverified_password', 'P@ssw0rd1!');"] } },
            { "listen": "test", "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": ["pm.test('status is 201', () => pm.response.to.have.status(201));"] } }
          ],
          "request": { "method": "POST", "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }, { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }], "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"display_name\": \"Unverified\", \"email\": \"{{lgn_unverified_email}}\", \"password\": \"{{lgn_unverified_password}}\"}", "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } } }, "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/register", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "register"] } }
        },
        {
          "name": "unverified account \u2192 403 email_not_verified",
          "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": ["pm.test('status is 403', () => pm.response.to.have.status(403));", "pm.test('code is email_not_verified', () => pm.expect(pm.response.json().code).to.eql('email_not_verified'));"] } }],
          "request": { "method": "POST", "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }, { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }], "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"identifier\": \"{{lgn_unverified_email}}\", \"password\": \"{{lgn_unverified_password}}\"}", "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } } }, "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "login"] } }
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "rate-limiting",
      "description": "Verifies the lgn:ip: IP rate limiter (burst=12, rate=12/15min).",
      "event": [{ "listen": "prerequest", "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": ["pm.collectionVariables.set('_xff', '127.0.0.1');"] } }],
      "item": [
        { "name": "warmup 1/12", "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": ["pm.test('not rate-limited yet (slot 1)', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.not.eql(429));"] } }], "request": { "method": "POST", "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }, { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }], "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"identifier\": \"\", \"password\": \"bad\"}", "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } } }, "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "login"] } } },
        { "name": "warmup 2/12", "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": ["pm.test('not rate-limited yet (slot 2)', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.not.eql(429));"] } }], "request": { "method": "POST", "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }, { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }], "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"identifier\": \"\", \"password\": \"bad\"}", "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } } }, "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "login"] } } },
        { "name": "warmup 3/12", "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": ["pm.test('not rate-limited yet (slot 3)', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.not.eql(429));"] } }], "request": { "method": "POST", "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }, { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }], "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"identifier\": \"\", \"password\": \"bad\"}", "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } } }, "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "login"] } } },
        { "name": "warmup 4/12", "event": [{ "listen": "test", "script": { "type": "text/javascript", "exec": ["pm.test('not rate-limited yet (slot 4)', () => pm.expect(pm.response.code).to.not.eql(429));"] } }], "request": { "method": "POST", "header": [{ "key": "Content-Type", "value": "application/json" }, { "key": "X-Forwarded-For", "value": "{{_xff}}" }], "body": { "mode": "raw", "raw": "{\"identifier\": \"\", \"password\": \"bad\"}", "options": { "raw": { "language": "json" } } }, "url": { "raw": "{{base_url}}/api/v1/auth/login", "host": ["{{base_url}}"], "path": ["api", "v1", "auth", "login"] } } },
